					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13056671#post-4506356</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13056671/scp-2454#post-4506356</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 18 Feb 2020 20:36:22 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RJB_R</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1229263</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I found the main description to be a little repetitive, with every paragraph being structured the same way. “The SCP-2454 instance has x property with y follow-up to x”. Not a deal breaker but it didn’t flow well and took me out of the piece. The interview, while not badly written, makes the piece go from a little clunky to outright boring by explaining everything.</p> <p>It’s unfortunate because the interview subject is clearly a character you put work into characterizing but he’s got nothing of substance to say beyond answering every question that the reader might be left wondering about.</p> <p>There’s room for more than one magic axolotl on the site but <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-1371">SCP-1371</a> does the same concept so much better by keeping it brief and letting the reader leave wondering rather than unsatisfied. Less is more, in this case.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
